==================================================
CURRENT WORK — Neovim-first practice workflow
Date: 2026-04-10
==================================================

==================================================
GOAL
==================================================

Make the Neovim plugin the primary daily-use surface for judge-loop.

The current direction is:

1. keep local-agent as the plugin's single local API boundary
2. let users browse and start problems directly from Neovim
3. cache solve buffers locally so work survives editor sessions
4. make submission errors and polling failures understandable
5. keep domain judge logic independent from infrastructure sandbox types

==================================================
CURRENT IMPLEMENTATION WORK
==================================================

1. LOCAL-AGENT PROBLEM PROXY

  Added local problem routes:
    GET /local/problems
    GET /local/problems/suggest
    GET /local/problems/:id

  These proxy to the api-server equivalents so the plugin does not need to call
  api-server directly.

2. NEOVIM HTTP CLIENT

  plugins/nvim-judge-loop/lua/judge-loop/agent.lua is being upgraded to:
    - capture HTTP status codes from curl
    - capture stderr
    - decode JSON responses
    - return structured errors as callback argument 3
    - expose problem list/detail/suggest calls

3. NEOVIM COMMANDS

  plugins/nvim-judge-loop/lua/judge-loop/commands.lua now includes:
    :JudgeUI
    :JudgeProblems
    :JudgeSuggest
    :JudgeLanguage [language]
    :JudgeStart [problem_id]
    :JudgeStop
    :JudgeSubmit
    :JudgeStatus
    :JudgeSync

  :JudgeStart <problem_id> now loads problem detail and opens a solve buffer.
  Without a problem id, it still starts a timer directly.

4. NEOVIM FLOATING UI

  plugins/nvim-judge-loop/lua/judge-loop/ui.lua is being expanded into a
  dependency-free floating workflow panel:
    - dashboard/status view
    - problem picker
    - suggested problem flow
    - problem detail view
    - source URL opening
    - timer stop
    - registry sync
    - submit current buffer

5. SOLVE BUFFER CACHE

  Solve buffers are cached under:
    ~/.judgeloopcache/<problem>/solution.<ext>

  Metadata is cached as:
    ~/.judgeloopcache/<problem>/problem.json

  The first open uses starter code when available. Later opens reuse the cached
  solution file. BufLeave saves the current solve buffer back to the cache.

6. LANGUAGE SWITCHING

  :JudgeLanguage can switch the active solve buffer between available starter
  languages, currently python and go.

7. JUDGE DOMAIN CLEANUP

  internal/domain/judge now owns RunResult.

  The outbound CodeRunner port returns judge.RunResult instead of depending on
  infrastructure/sandbox.RunResult. The sandbox adapter maps infrastructure
  output into the domain result type.

8. GO VERSION ALIGNMENT

  go.mod is now Go 1.26.0.

  The Docker sandbox Go image is being aligned to:
    golang:1.26.0-alpine

==================================================
